  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord spake unto Moses,.... After the murmurings of the Israelites by reason of the spies, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 14:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and their being threatened with a consumption of them in the wilderness on that account, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 14:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and their defeat at Hormah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 14:45",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and lest their posterity should be discouraged, and despair of ever enjoying the good land: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying; as follows. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "saying; as follows. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
